main event: A USAF C-47 pilot spotted a fast-moving, unidentified flat, white object near Santa Barbara, California on September 29, 1952.
interesting points: The object was seen for 30 seconds at an altitude of unknown feet.
The object had a high rate of speed and went up just before it disappeared.
The object had a flat trajectory.
The weather at the time of the sighting was clear and calm.
No other details about the object were provided in the report.
sighted object: a fast-moving, unidentified flat, white object
location: 6 miles southeast of Santa Barbara, California
